18.(1) The Director General shall prepare a National Disaster Risk Management Strategy which shall consist
* measures for the prevention of disasters and mitigation of their effects;
* measures to be taken for the integration of risk reduction and mitigation in development plans and projects at all levels;
* measures to be taken for preparedness and capacity building to effectively respond to any threat that has a potential to cause harm to human:, environment, property and livelihood;
* integrated disaster risk reduction strategies involving multi stakeholder participation;
* timely disaster risk reduction actions that contribute to sustainable development by limiting the loss of life and livelihood and environmental and property damage;
* the introduction of mechanisms to ensure transportation, utilities and public sector infrastructure networks are able to withstand potential threats; and
	* such other matters as may be prescribed.
